@ThinkingandTinkering   my grandfather remanufactured a Carter Car from the 1920's (1923? 🤔) that came from the factory with friction drive. The car probably weighed close to 1.5 tons (tonnes), and had a 4 cylinder engine around 2.5 liters and 10 horsepower.
The advertisements toted it as "having a million gears" back in the day, claiming that it was perfect for hill climbing, as it was always in the best power band for the load demand.
If you get a chance, Google it. 👍
